        "correctAnswer": "Direction: \\(\\langle 4, 13 \\rangle\\), Rate: \\(\\sqrt{185}\\)",
        "explanationParts": [
          "The direction of steepest increase is given by the gradient vector at that point.",
          "Compute partial derivatives: \\(f_x = 2xy\\), \\(f_y = x^2 + 3y^2\\).",
          "At \\((1,2)\\):",
          "\\(f_x = 2(1)(2) = 4\\), and \\(f_y = 1^2 + 3(2)^2 = 1 + 12 = 13\\).",
          "So the gradient is \\(\\nabla f(1,2) = \\langle 4, 13 \\rangle\\).",
          "The rate of increase is the **magnitude** of the gradient:",
          "\\[ ||\\nabla f|| = \\sqrt{4^2 + 13^2} = \\sqrt{16 + 169} = \\sqrt{185} \\]",
